// Hot/cold ISSU coverage. A tenant (db1) that existed BEFORE the upgrade has its
// durability written by the old binary and migrated (V1 -> V2) on boot of the new
// binary. It must survive a full SUSPEND -> COLD -> RESUME -> HOT round trip on the
// upgraded instance. SUSPEND/RESUME do not exist on the old binary, so this can only
// be exercised post-upgrade. Run as system_admin (multi-database DDL) on the default
// db, NOT while USE-ing db1 (an active db1 accessor would block the freeze).
// Data integrity is asserted by post_upgrade_db1.cypherl, which runs AFTER this file.
// With --storage-snapshot-on-exit=false (see values_template.yaml) the suspend writes
// no snapshot and RESUME reheats from WAL.
SUSPEND DATABASE db1;
RESUME DATABASE db1;
// Re-resuming an already-HOT database is idempotent success (returns the distinct
// "Database db1 is already resumed (HOT)." status, not an error).
RESUME DATABASE db1;
SHOW DATABASES;
